					<description><![CDATA[I really like your posts, James, so to the point and applicable.

I was at the dentist this morning and he told me a trick about flossing that I wanted to share with you. He said that I should floss BEFORE brushing my teeth. Because this way you make sure that toothpaste reaches more areas afterwards when you brush and more importantly in terms of creating a habit - because you will always brush your teeth after flossing, but you won&#039;t necessarily think you need to floss after brushing your teeth. Little trick that I&#039;m planning to test. Perhaps you&#039;re already doing this? It was a little light bulb for me and I&#039;m now holding tightly on to the thought that this is what will make my habit of flossing stick (even if in reality it might not be much of a psychological difference!) :)]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I really like your posts, James, so to the point and applicable.</p>
<p>I was at the dentist this morning and he told me a trick about flossing that I wanted to share with you. He said that I should floss BEFORE brushing my teeth. Because this way you make sure that toothpaste reaches more areas afterwards when you brush and more importantly in terms of creating a habit &#8211; because you will always brush your teeth after flossing, but you won&#8217;t necessarily think you need to floss after brushing your teeth. Little trick that I&#8217;m planning to test. Perhaps you&#8217;re already doing this? It was a little light bulb for me and I&#8217;m now holding tightly on to the thought that this is what will make my habit of flossing stick (even if in reality it might not be much of a psychological difference!) :)</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
