		<dc:creator><![CDATA[James]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 Feb 2013 06:11:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=3668#comment-376</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[James great post. Your approach a very similar process on how I made flossing a habit. However, I made it to hard for myself at the beginning.

Since I was flossing and using mouthwash and only the mouthwash was visible. So the pattern was to the wash then floss. It was working great until I ran out of mouthwash.

Since my workflow was broken I stop flossing. Afterwards I dropped the mouth wash and make the floss visible.

So now I am flossing regularly again. Now I make sure I have at least two boxes of floss so I never run out.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>James great post. Your approach a very similar process on how I made flossing a habit. However, I made it to hard for myself at the beginning.</p>
<p>Since I was flossing and using mouthwash and only the mouthwash was visible. So the pattern was to the wash then floss. It was working great until I ran out of mouthwash.</p>
<p>Since my workflow was broken I stop flossing. Afterwards I dropped the mouth wash and make the floss visible.</p>
<p>So now I am flossing regularly again. Now I make sure I have at least two boxes of floss so I never run out.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
