					<description><![CDATA[Spot on!

Just recently I swapped a bowl of chocolates with a bowl of oranges. Now, I never really liked sweets, but just as with your example with cookies, whenever I passed the table I would take one. Not surprisingly, after swapping, I started eating way more oranges :)

I actually did this without taking into consideration the effect on my diet, oranges just looked more aesthetically on the table, but it makes perfect sense now.

Rather intrigued with this, wonder what else I can find in how my surroundings affect my actions.

Cheers]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Spot on!</p>
<p>Just recently I swapped a bowl of chocolates with a bowl of oranges. Now, I never really liked sweets, but just as with your example with cookies, whenever I passed the table I would take one. Not surprisingly, after swapping, I started eating way more oranges :)</p>
<p>I actually did this without taking into consideration the effect on my diet, oranges just looked more aesthetically on the table, but it makes perfect sense now.</p>
<p>Rather intrigued with this, wonder what else I can find in how my surroundings affect my actions.</p>
<p>Cheers</p>
